**电脑罢工**

~~~
Describe a time when you had a problem with using the computer
You should say:
When it happened
Where it happened
What the problem was
And explain how you solved the problem at last
~~~

A few months ago, I had this really frustrating experience with my computer. It happened in college when I was trying to finish up a major project. My laptop was my lifeline for research and writing, so you can imagine how stressful it was.

The problem was that my computer would auto shutdown almost immediately after I turned it on. It was driving me crazy because I had no idea what was causing it. I thought it might be **some software issue**, but after some investigation, I realized it was a hardware problem.

I narrowed down the issue to either the battery or the hard disk. It took a bit of **troubleshooting** and research online, but I finally figured out that it was probably the hard disk overheating. It was a really unusual problem, but I didn't want to give up.

So, I decided to switch the positions of the two disks in my laptop, thinking it might help reduce the temperature of the one that was causing the issue. It was a bit **nerve-wracking** because I didn't want to mess things up even more, but it worked! By making that simple change, the overheating issue was resolved. This experience taught me a lot about troubleshooting computer problems.

